<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>MailChimp Contacts Formatter</title>
    <style>
        /* Add some spacing around the buttons */
        .upload-button {
          margin: 10px 0;  /* 10px space above and below each button */
          padding: 8px 16px; /* Slightly smaller padding than the submit button */
          font-size: 14px;  /* Smaller font size */
          background-color: #d3a6e0; /* Light purple color */
          color: white;  /* White text */
          border: none;  /* No border */
          border-radius: 5px;  /* Rounded corners */
          cursor: pointer;  /* Pointer cursor on hover */
          transition: background-color 0.3s ease; /* Smooth color transition */
        }

/* Hover effect for the upload buttons */
        .upload-button:hover {
          background-color: #c28cd1; /* Slightly darker purple when hovering */
        }


        .submit-button {
            background-color: #5a9bd5; /* Light blue color */
            color: white; /* Text color */
            font-weight: bold; /* Make text bold */
            padding: 12px 24px; /* Make button a little bigger */
            font-size: 16px; /* Adjust font size */
            border: none; /* Remove the border */
            border-radius: 5px; /* Rounded corners */
            cursor: pointer; /* Pointer cursor on hover */
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease; /* Smooth color transition */
        }

        /* Submit button hover effect */
        .submit-button:hover {
            background-color: #4c8cbf; /* Slightly darker blue when hovering */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Upload XPR Reports</h1>

    <% if error %>
      <p style="color: red;"><%= error %></p>
    <% end %>

    <form action="/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
      <label for="active">Active File:</label>
      <input type="file" name="active" id="active" class="upload-button" required><br>

      <label for="expired">Expired File:</label>
      <input type="file" name="expired" id="active" class="upload-button" required><br>

      <label for="users">Users File:</label>
      <input type="file" name="users" id="active" class="upload-button" required><br>

      <label for="old_file_data">Old File:</label>
      <input type="file" name="old_file_data" id="active" class="upload-button"><br>

      <input type="submit" value="Process Files" class="submit-button">
    </form>

    <div>
      <h2>Upload Instructions:</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Open <a href="https://www.sicabc.ca/xpr/">XPR</a> and login.</li>
        <li>In the left hand menu, navigate to RCA -> SICA Member Organizations.</li>
        <li>In the search bar, select Status -> Active.</li>
        <li>On the right hand side, click the cog and select Create Report.</li>
        <li>Once the blue bar has reached the end, click download.</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Upload this file to "Active file".</li>
          </ul>
        <li>In the search bar, select Status -> Expired.</li>
        <li>Repeat steps 4-5.
          <ul>
            <li>Upload this file to "Expired file".</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>In the left hand menu, navigate to Users -> SICA Member.</li>
        <li>Repeat steps 3-5.
          <ul>
            <li>Upload this file to "Users file".</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>For "Old file", upload the previous CSV that was uploaded to this MailChimp audience.
          <ul>
            <li>This would have been a file generated by this site.</li>
            <li>If you do not have it, that's okay.</li>
            <li>Beware that any contacts removed from XPR since the last upload will not be marked for removal in MailChimp.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Click "Process Files" and follow instructions on the next page.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
